LAGOS – A detachment of heavily armed police operatives on Monday afternoon took over the surroundings of the All Progressives Congress (APC) National Secretariat in Abuja. This came moments after a letter written by Governor Mai Mala Buni-led Caretaker Extra-Ordinary Convention Planning Committee (CECPC) to the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) announcing the indefinite postponement of its national convention was leaked. Heavily armed police operatives are currently positioned within the secretariat along Blantyre Street, Wuse 2, Abuja, following a security report that certain persons had been mobilised to stage demonstrations against the Caretaker committee. Nigerians, APC Members Tired Of Convention Postponement –… However, an official at the party secretariat told DAILY INDEPENDENT that while all is calm in the secretariat, the security was beefed up to forestall possible attacks. “There has always been adequate security presence here. But I noticed there have been additional security forces around the vicinity since 12 pm. Everything is calm as of now”.